name: Manco Cápac
description: Manco Cápac, by the stories, was the first ruler of Cusco-Peru and that later would become the Inca Empire. He ruled for 30 years and it was he who banned human sacrifice, murder, theft among other crimes, he also established the worship of the sun. In the legends it was said that he was the son of Inti (Sun God) and that he was sent to our world and appeared in Lake Titicaca carrying the Tapac-yauri a golden staff.
